name: KMS Elbe (Azur Lane)
description:
Updated Mar/16/2023:

New version trained with DAdapt optimizer on animefull-latest. Reduced file size & improved compatibility, however details (gradient eyes, dress side cutout) seem to fluctuate even more in contrast to overfitting in the first release. Making ends meet sure ain't easy.

Features bestest faux-mesugaki KMS Elbe from Azur Lane in her original costume, trained on ACertainModel.

Her recent valentine casual costume, Pure-Hearted Bad Girl has not been trained due to very few artworks being available, yet is possible to recreate due to its composition being rather generic (see prompts).

Release v1.0 was tested through the mid-high weight range, works fine from 0.5 with decent level of flexibility for outfits, poses, etc. to circa 0.9 where overfitting becomes noticeable on some SD checkpoints.

Release V2.0 was tested and works well on full weight (1.0).

Prompts

  • Base: elbeazln, peaked cap, two side up, black layered dress, black gloves, thighhighs, boots

  • Undergarment: white leotard, black gloves, thighhighs

    (black corset can be moved to negative prompt if undesired)

  • Valentine costume: yellow or brown off-shoulder sweater, pencil skirt, garter straps, thighhighs

  • For enhancing details: frills, chain, streaked hair

Known issue:

Clothing have a tendency of sticking to the original black & white color palette regardless of prompt or weight applied. I currently am not aware of any solution that doesn't lead to underlearning.
